    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is a neutral holding place where funds—like your down payment and closing costs—are temporarily stored by a neutral third party until all conditions for the sale are met. Your realtor needs this to ensure money isn't transferred until the seller has confirmed they want to proceed and the buyer has arranged payment. It protects both parties by preventing one side from getting stuck with unfulfilled obligations while the closing date approaches. Ultimately, once the deal is finalized, the escrow account releases the funds directly to the seller (minus agreed-upon fees and prorations) to officially close the transaction.",
