    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so it's basically just a way for someone else to guard the money so nobody gets ripped off? who actually manages the account and how do i know the money is safe there?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, that's exactly right; escrow acts as a financial handshake to ensure you and the seller aren't blindsided during the exchange. The account is managed by a licensed title company or an escrow officer, legally bound to follow strict statutes that prohibit them from using the funds for their own benefit. You can verify safety by reviewing your closing disclosures, which list these professionals, and by checking that the title company provides a duplicate final statement detailing every dollar moved upon completion.",
