    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. so the title company is like the middleman keeping everything secure. what happens if there is a dispute during the closing process though? like if the seller claims they didn't get enough or if some repairs weren't actually done? does the escrow officer just hold onto the money forever or how is that settled?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If a dispute arises, the escrow officer pauses the release of funds and holds the money until the parties agree on a resolution percentage or legal intervention occurs. In severe conflicts, the process may shift to mediation or arbitration where an independent third party decides how to distribute the escrowed amount. While this can cause delays, the officer is not legally required to wait forever and will typically coordinate with the title company or lender to expedite the matter so the transaction can eventually close.",
